<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5723] Problem with cached calls with GroovyServlet</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5723</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A couple users reported problems since Groovy 2.0.2 with the GroovyServlet:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/glaforge/gaelyk/issues/163&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/glaforge/gaelyk/issues/163&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When using Gaelyk on Google App Engine, they noticed that the first hit for a certain groovlet would run fine, while all subsequent calls would fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem started appearing after the changes operated on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5125&quot; title=&quot;GroovyScriptEngine load from  jarURL fail&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-5125&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-5125&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which fixed an issue when using scripts stored in a JAR with GroovyScriptEngine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem can be fixed by amending AbstractHttpServlet.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Google App Engine with the Gaelyk framework</environment>
